Health economic evaluation of primary human papillomavirus screening in urban 
populations in China.

Keane A(1), Shi JF(2), Simms KT(3), Liu YJ(4), Lew JB(3), Mazariego C(3), Yuill 
S(3), Wu RF(5), Liu ZH(6), Zhao FH(7), Jeronimo J(8), Canfell K(9), Qiao YL(7).

Author information:
(1)Cancer Research Division, Cancer Council New South Wales, Sydney, Australia; 
School of Public Health, University of Sydney, Sydney, Australia. Electronic 
address: Adam.Keane@nswcc.org.au.
(2)Department of Epidemiology, National Cancer Center, National Clinical 
Research Center for Cancer, Cancer Hospital, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences 
and Peking Union Medical College, Beijing, China; Office of Cancer Screening, 
National Cancer Center, National Clinical Research Center for Cancer, Cancer 
Hospital, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences and Peking Union Medical College, 
Beijing, China.
(3)Cancer Research Division, Cancer Council New South Wales, Sydney, Australia; 
School of Public Health, University of Sydney, Sydney, Australia.
(4)School of Public Health, Zunyi Medical University, Zunyi, China.
(5)Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Peking University Shenzhen Hospital, 
Shenzhen, China.
(6)Department of Gynecology, Shenzhen Maternity and Child Healthcare Hospital, 
Shenzhen, China.
(7)Department of Epidemiology, National Cancer Center, National Clinical 
Research Center for Cancer, Cancer Hospital, Chinese Academy of Medical Sciences 
and Peking Union Medical College, Beijing, China.
(8)Consultant for the US National Cancer Institute Bethesda, Maryland, USA.
(9)Cancer Research Division, Cancer Council New South Wales, Sydney, Australia; 
