To examine the suitability of Myzus persicae, Lipaphis erysimi, Semiaphis 
heraclei and Aphis gossypii to propagation of Harmonia axyridis population, we 
studied the development and reproduction of this ladybird by constructing 
two-sex life table in the laboratory with those four aphid species as diet. The 
results showed that the immature duration of H. axyridis decreased in an order 
of L. erysimi (18.18 d), A. gossypii (17.48 d), S. heraclei (16.23 d), and M. 
persicae (15.77 d). The survival rates of preadult period were S. heraclei 
(88.3%), M. persicae (86.7%), L. ery-simi (55.0%), and A. gossypii (55.0%). The 
fecundity of those species were S. heraclei (1750.5), M. persicae (1441.5), A. 
