S. heraclei (78.8 d), M. persicae (63.1 d), A. gossypii (54.3 d), and L. erysimi 
(48.4 d). The intrinsic rate of increase (rm) of H. axyridis population 
decreased in an order of M. persicae (0.19), S. heraclei (0.18), L. erysimi 
(0.14), and A. gossypii (0.14). The net reproduction rates (R0) were S. heraclei 
(895.83), M. persicae (600.62), L. erysimi (273.47), and A. gossypii (268.33). 
Among those four aphid species, S. heraclei and M. persicae were more suitable 
for the propagation of H. axyridis population.

